<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-8563888538941330867'>
<p>
This is some extremely interesting work.  I am an experienced C++ programmer, and I share your pains, but some of the things you can do with templates are just too awesome to pass up.  I&#39;ve been loving boost::variant these days, but dear God has it wrecked my compile times!  It seems like something equivalent could be implemented with c-amplify relatively painlessly, and without the massive compile times associated with C++ templates.  Plus, the automatic header generation would be just delightful.<br /><br />Any chance that you&#39;ll ever open-source your prototype?
</p>
