<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-1326663320906894757'>
<p>
Look at <a href="http://super.para.media.kyoto-u.ac.jp/~tasuku/sc/index.html" rel="nofollow">SC</a><br />This is expandable C in lisp with lisp syntax where you can use lisp style <br />macroses and define your own constructs.<br /><br />It help me a lot in generating my C projects.<br /><br />Example of function in SC:<br /><br />(def (fib n) (fn int int)<br />  (if (&lt;= n 2) <br />      (return 1)<br />      (return (+ (fib (- n 2))<br />                 (fib (- n 1))))))<br /><br />=&gt;<br /><br />int fib (int n)<br />{<br />  if (n &lt;= 2)<br />    return 1;<br />  else<br />    return fib (n - 2) + fib (n - 1);<br />}<br /><br />Structure declaration in SC:<br /><br />((struct list)<br />  (data int)<br />  (next (ptr (struct list))))<br /><br />Example of macro in SC:<br /><br />(%defmacro ntimes (n &amp;body form)<br />    `(for ((def i int 0) (&lt; i ,n) (inc i)) ,@form))
</p>
</dd>
