<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-5617554425113126797'>
<p>
&gt; Johan Kotlinski said...<br />&gt; How do you think Lisp is an improvement <br />&gt; over C++ in this regard? <br />&gt; In my experience Lisp is more like <br />&gt; &quot;everyone sees everything,&quot; <br />&gt; no real support for information hiding<br />&gt; besides wrapping stuff inside functions.<br /><br />You can use packages, they have protected(internal) and public(exported) symbols.<br /><br />For CLOS classes and generics with 50<br />lines of MOP you can add private slots/methods, &quot;friend&quot; slots/methods <br />or any other sort of protection you like.<br /><br />But nobody really need it as I can see.
</p>
</dd>
